Your favourite record has fallen off the table and is rolling down a [`[$theta]^\circ`] inclined slope. Fortunately
your safety spring is attached for just this reason and will prevent it from rolling too far. The spring has a
stiffness of [`k = [$k]\ \textrm{N/m}`] and the record can be approximated by a thin uniform disc with radius 
[`r = [$r]\ \textrm{m}`]. It started a distance [`d_1 = [$d1]\ \textrm{m}`] from the wall and rolls down
the slope without slipping at an initial velocity of [`v = [$v]\ \textrm{m/s}`]. If the spring has an unstretched length of [`[$uL]\ \textrm{m}`]
and the record comes to a stop after rolling [`[$d]\ \textrm{m}`] find the mass of your favourite record.


